                    <div class="chapter-section mt-5">
                        <h4 class="text-primary fw-bold mb-3">The Path Planning Process</h4>

                        <div class="planning-process-container mt-4">
                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">1</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Identify Start and End Points</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-0">Clearly identify where you'll pick up the load and where it needs to be delivered.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">2</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Review Available Routes</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-0">Identify possible routes between start and end points. There may be several options.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">3</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Walk Each Route</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-0">Physically walk from start point to end point via each possible route. Observe all conditions and hazards.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">4</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Assess Each Route</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-2">For each possible route, evaluate:</p>
                                    <ul class="mb-0">
                                        <li>Is it wide enough?</li>
                                        <li>Are height clearances adequate?</li>
                                        <li>What is the surface condition?</li>
                                        <li>Are there blind spots?</li>
                                        <li>How many hazards are present?</li>
                                        <li>How much pedestrian traffic?</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">5</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Select Primary Route</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-2">Choose the route that offers:</p>
                                    <ul class="mb-0">
                                        <li>Best overall safety</li>
                                        <li>Adequate clearances</li>
                                        <li>Good visibility</li>
                                        <li>Minimal hazards</li>
                                        <li>Suitable surfaces</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p class="mt-2 mb-0"><em>Note: The shortest route is not always the safest route.</em></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">6</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Identify Alternative Route</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-0">Always have a backup plan. What if your primary route becomes blocked? Plan at least one alternative.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">7</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Measure Critical Clearances</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-2">For tight spots, use a measuring tape to verify:</p>
                                    <ul class="mb-0">
                                        <li>Actual aisle width vs. required width</li>
                                        <li>Actual height clearance vs. required clearance</li>
                                    </ul>
                                    <p class="mt-2 mb-0"><strong>Don't guess - measure and be sure.</strong></p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">8</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Document Your Plan</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-0">Some workplaces require travel path planning to be documented, especially for complex or high-risk moves. Even if not required, making notes helps ensure you don't forget important details.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">9</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Communicate Your Plan</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-2">Inform relevant people of your intended route:</p>
                                    <ul class="mb-0">
                                        <li>Your supervisor</li>
                                        <li>Other forklift operators</li>
                                        <li>Workers in the area</li>
                                        <li>Security or traffic controllers</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <div class="planning-step">
                                <div class="planning-step-number">10</div>
                                <div class="planning-step-content">
                                    <h6 class="fw-bold">Conduct Final Check</h6>
                                    <p class="mb-0">Before starting, do a final walk-through to ensure nothing has changed since you planned your route.</p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="chapter-section mt-5">
                        <h4 class="text-primary fw-bold mb-3">Making Route Decisions</h4>
                        <p class="mb-4">When choosing between routes, consider:</p>

                        <div class="route-decision-grid">
                            <div class="route-decision-card">
                                <h6 class="route-decision-title">üõ°Ô∏è Safety First</h6>
                                <p class="mb-0">A longer, safer route is always better than a shorter, riskier route. <strong>Never compromise safety for speed.</strong></p>
                            </div>

                            <div class="route-decision-card">
                                <h6 class="route-decision-title">üõ§Ô∏è Surface Quality</h6>
