                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="chapter-section mt-5">
                        <h4 class="text-primary fw-bold mb-3">Dealing with Inadequate Clearances</h4>
                        <p class="mb-3">If clearances are insufficient:</p>
                        <ul class="mb-3">
                            <li>Find an alternative route</li>
                            <li>Reduce load size (if possible)</li>
                            <li>Remove or relocate obstacles (if safe and authorized)</li>
                            <li>Use different equipment better suited to the space</li>
                            <li>Report to supervisor if no safe option exists</li>
                        </ul>
                        <div class="alert alert-danger">
                            <strong>‚ö†Ô∏è Never force your way through inadequate clearances.</strong> Damage to loads, equipment, or structures will result.
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="chapter-section mt-5">
                        <h4 class="text-primary fw-bold mb-3">Responding to Route Blockages</h4>
                        <p class="mb-3">If your planned route becomes blocked:</p>
                        <ul class="mb-3">
                            <li>Stop safely</li>
                            <li>Assess the situation</li>
                            <li>Switch to your alternative route if suitable</li>
                            <li>Wait for blockage to clear if alternative isn't available</li>
                            <li>Communicate with others about the delay</li>
                            <li>Never create new, unplanned routes without proper assessment</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

